Ian Jackson 2024-25 Regular Season Highlights | North Carolina Guard
North Carolina guard Ian Jackson burst onto the scene with a productive year during the 2024-25 campaign. Jackson finished the season averaging 12.3 points, 2.8 rebounds, and 0.9 assists per game while shooting 46% from the floor and 40% from three-point range. Midway through the season, the freshman went on a run where he scored 20 or more points in 6 of 7 games. Take a look at highlights from a fantastic rookie season in the ACC right here.
